00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:34,520
If you don't truly love me.

283
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:36,640
you can tell me honestly.

284
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,160
If maybe.

285
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,640
your heart.

286
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:41,920
still belongs to your ex.

287
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:43,600
then at least I'll know.

288
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,800
that she's.

289
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:47,320
the reason you don't want to marry me.

290
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:49,120
What do you think?

291
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,760
I'm sorry.

292
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:55,120
that I'm still not brave enough
to tell you the truth right now.

293
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:56,960
I just...

294
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:59,200
don't want my past.

295
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,520
to ruin your happiness.

296
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:03,120
Once.

297
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:06,000
I've dealt with the clip situation properly.

298
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:08,640
I'll tell you everything.

299
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,720
I'll wait.

300
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:14,320
until the day you tell me the truth.

301
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:17,840
It's nothing, really.

302
00:20:18,840 --> 00:20:20,320
Let's go to sleep.

303
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,040
I'm sleepy already.

304
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:45,680
Noo Si.

305
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,240
Noo Si.

306
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:48,640
Noo Si.

307
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:51,120
Babe.

308
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:53,280
Where are you going this early?

309
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:54,840
You're not going to make merit again, are you?

310
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:58,920
Nooo, I'm still sleepy.
Let me sleep a little longer.

311
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,200
I have to rush back to Suphan Buri.

312
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,880
Jiw's family called and said.

313
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,560
she's not doing too well.

314
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,320
They want me to go check on her.

315
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,840
And I'm borrowing your shirt, okay?

316
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:12,200
Of course, babe. But...

317
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,960
you're leaving right now?

318
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,440
I'm scared I won't make it in time.

319
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:16,840
Do you want to come with me?

320
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:19,160
I really want to, babe, but...

321
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,360
I have a meeting with the contractor today.

322
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,960
And today is literally the only day he's free.

323
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,240
After this he's going overseas for a long time.

324
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:28,720
I'm worried about Jiw.

325
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:31,440
And I don't want you driving alone either.

326
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:32,520
I'm worried about you.

327
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,520
It's okay, babe. You stay and handle work.

328
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:37,440
I'll drive carefully, and...

329
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:39,480
I'll keep updating you about Jiw.

330
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:41,000
All right then.

331
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,200
Keep me posted, okay?

332
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:44,680
Once I'm done, I'll rush over right away.

333
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:46,320
I'm heading out now.

334
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:52,040
Drive safely, babe.

335
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:07,240
Hello? What's going on?

336
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:09,240
I just finished talking with the contractor.

337
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,000
How's Jiw?

338
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:12,280
Is she okay?

339
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:13,480
Um...

340
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:14,880
Babe...

341
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:17,320
I mean...

342
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,000
You...

343
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,680
Why do you sound like that?

344
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:24,920
Is something wrong with Jiw?

345
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:26,120
Well...

346
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,280
There's something I need to tell you.

347
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,120
I was gonna say...

348
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:37,960
I need to bring Jon back to live with us.

349
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,000
It's just that...

350
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:41,280
my brother can't really
take care of him anymore.

351
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:42,880
Oh.

352
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,760
I thought something happened to Jiw.

353
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,880
Turns out it's about Jon.

354
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:49,480
But are you really okay with it...

355
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:51,640
if Jon moves back in with us?

356
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:55,360
Of course, babe. I'm more than okay with it.

357
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:56,920
Honestly...

358
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:59,920
this has been on my mind for a while too.

359
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:02,120
I was scared Jon might think...

360
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,360
you chose me over him...

361
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,560
even though he was here before me.

362
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,520
You don't have to worry, okay?

363
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:11,200
Okay. Hearing that really...

364
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,720
makes me feel better.

365
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:15,080
So...

366
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:16,280
what about Jiw?

367
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,120
How's Jiw doing?

368
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:19,760
He's doing better now.

369
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:22,400
But he'll probably need to stay
at the hospital a few more days

370
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,880
before he can go home.

371
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:26,720
Phew. That's a relief.

372
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:29,360
So when are you coming back to me?

373
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:31,120
You're done with everything already, right?

374
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:33,320
I'm hurrying back right now, babe.

375
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:35,440
I already miss you.

376
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,240
What is this?

377
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:39,640
We've only been apart for
a few hours and you miss me already?

378
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:43,360
Come on. Even one minute away from you

379
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:45,640
feels way too long for me.

380
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:49,800
If I could teleport

381
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:52,400
I'd teleport straight to you right now.

382
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,520
Well, if I could teleport too

383
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:57,120
I'd teleport to you as well.

384
00:23:58,320 --> 00:23:59,400
Okay, enough.

385
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:02,040
If we keep flirting like this,
we'll never get to see each other.

386
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:05,000
I'm packing up and heading home right now.

387
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,000
Wait for me at home, okay?

388
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,480
I'll be back as fast as I can.

389
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:09,920
Okay.

390
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:30,120
Why are you here?

391
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,160
Hey, mistress, help me inside
your house already.

392
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:39,280
Who's the mistress here? Watch your mouth.

393
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:42,240
What? Did I say something wrong?

394
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:47,640
If the one who came later isn't called
a mistress, then what is she called?

395
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:50,480
Hey, Jane.

396
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:51,960
How did you get here?

397
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,640
Well, my girlfriend disappeared.

398
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:59,520
So I came here to see if she was here.

399
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:01,680
And you don't have to wonder

400
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,640
whether she and I know each other.

401
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:04,680
Yeah, we do.

402
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,240
We've met at the restaurant
and just talked recently.

403
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:09,040
We know everything.

404
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:11,760
What are you even talking about?

405
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:14,240
I already told you we broke up,
so why are you still bothering me?

406
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:17,280
Don't listen to her.

407
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:19,280
We broke up a long time ago.

408
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,680
She's the one who won't stop bothering me.

409
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,520
Bothering you?

410
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:27,160
Did you forget that you invited me
to the mall the other day?

411
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:30,080
And you secretly came out to see me

412
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:32,480
while she was trying clothes
on in the fitting room.

413
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,280
Stop making things up.

414
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:35,520
Go home already.

415
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:37,080
We can talk later.

416
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:39,080
You heard that loud and clear, right?

417
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:41,440
"We can talk later" means
we never really broke up.

418
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:42,560
We're still talking.

419
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:44,760
- Come on.
- Jane.

420
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:47,160
Don't listen to her.

421
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,440
Go inside first. I'll handle this myself.

422
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:50,520
Go on.

423
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:52,760
Si.

424
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:56,360
Why are you in such a hurry to chase her away?

425
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:57,640
You keep pushing her away.

426
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:00,400
What are you scared of?

427
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:06,320
Stop talking so much.

428
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,760
I told you to leave, so leave.

429
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:08,920
Go.

430
00:26:09,040 --> 00:26:10,560
I'm not leaving. If I go, we go together.

431
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:12,680
- Jane.
- Shut up and go home already.

432
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:14,920
This is my house. If you don't leave

433
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,240
I'm calling the police.

434
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:17,760
Your house?

435
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:20,960
I'm still out on the street.
I haven't even stepped into your house yet.

436
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,720
You know you can't report me for that, right?

437
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:28,240
What a shame.

438
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:30,640
Too bad you've never seen

439
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:32,680
how happy we were together.

440
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,400
Stop it.

441
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:37,120
Should I show her right now?

442
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,920
Or should I let her look it up online herself?

443
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:41,560
Just go home already and stop bothering me.

444
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:44,760
- Did you seriously just shove me?
- Why wouldn't I?

445
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:46,680
A terrible person like you

446
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:48,560
deserves way worse than this.

447
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,520
- Go.
- Hey, Jane.

448
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,040
- Jane, Jane.
- Come on. We're settling this right now.

449
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:53,760
- Let go of me.
- Move.

450
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:54,960
Jane.

451
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,720
Don't. Stay out of this.

452
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,520
- Si, come on.
- Let me go.

453
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:05,640
- You really punched me?
- P'Klao. P'Klao.

454
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:07,200
P'Klao. P'Klao.

455
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,280
Damn right I did.

456
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:11,200
One punch and your brain already
stopped working?

457
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:13,400
Or do you want another one?

458
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:26,440
Does it hurt?

459
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:29,160
It hurts so bad.

460
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:31,880
I might actually die from this.

461
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:35,400
Hey. Stop joking around already.

462
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:37,200
I'm seriously worried about you.

463
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:43,520
So then...

464
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:45,960
why...

465
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:47,960
didn't you tell me last night

466
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,720
that you ran into Jane?

467
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:55,120
Because I didn't want you to feel upset.

468
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:59,560
But you believe me, right?

469
00:28:00,840 --> 00:28:03,280
When I say I already broke up with her.

470
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:06,640
Then...

471
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,400
say it to me again.

472
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:12,200
Tell me you really broke up with her.

473
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:15,400
Because whatever you say

474
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,880
I'll believe every word.

475
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,560
I already broke up with her, babe.

476
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:23,960
A long time ago too.

477
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:26,800
It's all in the past now.

478
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:30,600
Okay then...

479
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:34,080
I'll believe you.

480
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:37,200
Thank you, babe.

481
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:42,560
But...

482
00:28:43,120 --> 00:28:44,720
there's one more thing

483
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,320
I want to know.

484
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:49,080
What do you want to know?

485
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:52,240
I already told Mom before

486
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:54,120
that I didn't feel anything for her.

487
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:57,840
Right now, I'm just trying
to get that country girl

488
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,600
Klao

489
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:02,320
to renew the contract
with us as soon as possible.

490
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,480
I'm sorry, babe.

491
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:11,760
I didn't mean it like that.

492
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:12,840
It's just...

493
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:15,880
that was when we had only just met.

494
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:18,560
I admit it.

495
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:21,480
I really did think that way before.

496
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,520
But that was only because

497
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:27,320
I wanted my parents
to see that I could do it.

498
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:29,760
But...

499
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:34,400
once I actually got to meet you and know you

500
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:38,000
I realized I was wrong.

501
00:29:40,360 --> 00:29:41,840
You're a good person.

502
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:46,960
You truly love me and you're sincere with me.

503
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:51,320
It's okay.

504
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:54,440
I've never been mad at you.

505
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:58,160
No matter what your reason was

506
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:01,200
I still would've married you anyway.

507
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:04,040
Because I was sure

508
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:07,200
that I could make you fall in love with me.

509
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:17,360
P'Klao.

510
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,000
Hm?

511
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:21,440
But...

512
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:24,880
there's still something else

513
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:27,680
you don't know.

514
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:30,200
What is it?

515
00:30:32,760 --> 00:30:34,080
Jane has videos...

516
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:37,600
from when I was with her.

517
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,280
I'm scared.

518
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:43,600
Scared she'll post the clips online.

519
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:46,960
So...

520
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,400
have those clips been around for a long time?

521
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,400
Yeah, a long time.

522
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:02,520
Back when I was still dating her.

523
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:06,200
She probably set up a camera

524
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:07,840
without me knowing.

525
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,680
She was probably planning to blackmail me.

526
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:14,280
Forget it.

527
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:16,040
I don't care.

528
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,320
But she threatened me, babe.

529
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:22,920
She said...

530
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:26,800
if I don't break up with you

531
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:28,520
and get back together with her

532
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:32,040
she'll release all the clips.

533
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,240
Then...

534
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:38,480
should we go to the police?

535
00:31:38,520 --> 00:31:40,000
No, babe.

536
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:43,480
She's completely unhinged.

537
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:45,000
If we do anything

538
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:47,400
that makes her angry

539
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,800
she might release the clips immediately.

540
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:52,280
And if she releases them...

541
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:56,400
my parents will be disappointed in me.

542
00:31:57,800 --> 00:32:00,720
You might even be embarrassed
to have me as your girlfriend.

543
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:03,480
I don't even know
how I can face anyone anymore.

544
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:04,560
Noo Si.

545
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:06,560
I really don't care about that stuff.

546
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,600
What I care about is you.

547
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,200
I'm scared.

548
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:14,080
I don't know...

549
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:17,720
how I'll be able to face anyone.

550
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:24,120
Don't cry, okay?

551
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:26,360
How about this...

552
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:29,520
Just stay calm for now.

553
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:31,200
Don't do anything impulsive.

554
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:33,280
And...

555
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:36,120
don't meet or contact that woman again.

556
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:38,960
I promise...

557
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:41,320
I'll help you deal with this myself.

558
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:45,160
I'm sorry.

559
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:48,880
For making you disappointed in me.

