00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:13,920
You little leech.

832
00:48:13,920 --> 00:48:15,360
What are you doing here?

833
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:18,480
Just capturing the moment.

834
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:22,120
Wait. What is all this?

835
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:23,640
Over there, over there.

836
00:48:23,720 --> 00:48:26,320
Please step this way.

837
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:28,360
- Bro.
- Sweet as syrup.

838
00:48:29,040 --> 00:48:31,920
Sweet as syrup.

839
00:48:32,280 --> 00:48:33,960
Was this your plan?

840
00:48:34,440 --> 00:48:36,960
It's a surprise.

841
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:38,480
Surprise.

842
00:48:40,440 --> 00:48:41,440
Hey.

843
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:43,440
You and her.

844
00:48:43,720 --> 00:48:46,040
planned this whole thing just
to trick me into putting on makeup.

845
00:48:46,080 --> 00:48:47,360
So that you could...

846
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:50,000
Close your eyes first.

847
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:51,480
Close them.

848
00:48:51,840 --> 00:48:53,680
What are you planning to do to me now?

849
00:48:53,720 --> 00:48:55,880
Just close your eyes first.

850
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:12,600
You can open them now.

851
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:16,760
Can I open my eyes yet?

852
00:49:18,440 --> 00:49:19,560
You can now.

853
00:49:21,160 --> 00:49:22,800
Sweet as syrup.

854
00:49:36,480 --> 00:49:38,560
Actually, I had.

855
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:41,920
my sisters-in-law help pick it out for me.

856
00:49:42,040 --> 00:49:44,920
I was scared that if I
chose it myself, it'd look cheesy.

857
00:49:44,960 --> 00:49:46,760
And I was worried you wouldn't like it.

858
00:49:54,280 --> 00:49:58,120
Honestly, I wanted to buy you a gold ring.

859
00:49:58,280 --> 00:49:59,880
But my sister-in-law said.

860
00:49:59,920 --> 00:50:01,600
a classy woman like you.

861
00:50:01,640 --> 00:50:03,040
deserves a diamond ring.

862
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:05,160
So I ended up with this one.

863
00:50:05,360 --> 00:50:07,960
I don't know if you'll like it though.

864
00:50:08,600 --> 00:50:11,880
Whether it's a diamond ring or a gold ring.

865
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:13,920
I love them all as long as it's from you.

866
00:50:19,200 --> 00:50:21,280
If you're saying that.

867
00:50:21,320 --> 00:50:24,080
does that mean you'll marry me?

868
00:50:30,840 --> 00:50:32,280
Come on.

869
00:50:33,680 --> 00:50:36,560
Wait. Why though?

870
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:39,680
I went through all the trouble
of setting up this whole band.

871
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:41,800
and gathered half the village here.

872
00:50:41,840 --> 00:50:45,080
Wasn't it amazing enough
for you to agree to marry me?

873
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:01,720
Oh. Kneeling.

874
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:03,520
Oh.

875
00:51:09,680 --> 00:51:12,240
Little Si, will you marry me?

876
00:51:21,280 --> 00:51:23,320
I do.

877
00:51:38,360 --> 00:51:41,240
It's okay. Calm down, okay?

878
00:51:43,480 --> 00:51:44,920
You can do it.

879
00:51:45,920 --> 00:51:48,240
She said yes. She said yes.

880
00:51:53,240 --> 00:51:56,080
- It's okay. Calm down.
- Don't fight each other.

881
00:51:56,120 --> 00:51:57,120
- P'Klao.
- Oh my god.

882
00:51:57,120 --> 00:51:58,920
Klao, calm down.

883
00:51:59,960 --> 00:52:01,720
Don't let your hands shake.

884
00:52:02,120 --> 00:52:03,320
Klao, aim carefully.

885
00:52:06,120 --> 00:52:07,840
Oh my goodness.

886
00:52:09,600 --> 00:52:11,240
- Klao, calm down.
- Give her a chance.

887
00:52:14,280 --> 00:52:16,600
P'Klao, calm down. Take a deep breath.

888
00:52:17,000 --> 00:52:19,440
It'd be so embarrassing if the ring won't go on.

889
00:52:20,200 --> 00:52:22,840
You can do it, boss. You've got this.

890
00:52:35,080 --> 00:52:38,040
I'm getting married.

891
00:52:46,080 --> 00:52:49,240
- They're telling us to kiss.
- Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.

892
00:52:49,240 --> 00:52:51,880
Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.

893
00:52:53,280 --> 00:52:54,520
Thank you so much.

894
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:23,120
Are you sleepy yet?

895
00:53:23,240 --> 00:53:24,320
Not yet.

896
00:53:26,480 --> 00:53:28,000
Wow.

897
00:53:28,240 --> 00:53:30,640
You've been touching that ring so much
the diamond's gonna wear out.

898
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:35,840
You know.

899
00:53:36,680 --> 00:53:37,920
Back then.

900
00:53:38,160 --> 00:53:39,440
if I ever got married.

901
00:53:40,200 --> 00:53:42,000
that person.

902
00:53:42,280 --> 00:53:43,640
would've had to give me.

903
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:47,400
at least a ten-carat diamond ring.

904
00:53:48,880 --> 00:53:49,920
But now.

905
00:53:50,280 --> 00:53:51,520
right now.

906
00:53:52,440 --> 00:53:54,280
as long as it's you, that's enough.

907
00:53:55,440 --> 00:53:58,440
I would've married you
no matter what ring you gave me.

908
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:03,760
Talking sweet like that deserves a reward.

909
00:54:13,720 --> 00:54:17,120
Maybe I should order a ring for you too.

910
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:21,400
Nah. I don't like wearing rings.

911
00:54:21,400 --> 00:54:23,400
Huh? Why not?

912
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:25,400
I'm wearing one, you know.

913
00:54:25,680 --> 00:54:27,320
If you wear one too.

914
00:54:27,760 --> 00:54:30,360
other women won't dare flirt with you.

915
00:54:31,720 --> 00:54:33,440
Rings don't suit me.

916
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:35,600
I spend my days covered in dirt and mud.

917
00:54:42,160 --> 00:54:43,760
Why did you go quiet?

918
00:54:43,920 --> 00:54:45,560
Did I say something wrong?

919
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:49,160
Not at all.

920
00:54:49,440 --> 00:54:50,920
I was just.

921
00:54:51,120 --> 00:54:52,720
thinking that.

922
00:54:52,720 --> 00:54:55,120
maybe the reason
you don't like diamond rings.

923
00:54:55,520 --> 00:54:57,040
is because.

924
00:54:58,840 --> 00:54:59,920
you yourself.

925
00:55:00,240 --> 00:55:01,360
are the diamond.

926
00:55:03,640 --> 00:55:04,880
And.

927
00:55:05,000 --> 00:55:08,520
you're the most beautiful diamond of all.

928
00:55:08,720 --> 00:55:10,920
and the rarest one too.

929
00:55:14,320 --> 00:55:16,520
But you're also.

930
00:55:16,520 --> 00:55:18,520
the person who found this diamond.

931
00:55:19,200 --> 00:55:21,680
And the only one.

932
00:55:21,720 --> 00:55:23,640
who gets to keep it.

933
00:55:27,640 --> 00:55:28,880
From now on.

934
00:55:29,360 --> 00:55:31,920
we're only going to be happy together.

935
00:55:56,160 --> 00:55:57,920
Hey. You little leech.

936
00:55:59,120 --> 00:56:00,640
Hey, stop the car.

937
00:56:01,400 --> 00:56:02,520
Stop first.

938
00:56:03,800 --> 00:56:05,440
Hey, pork tapeworm. Stop.

939
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:08,600
Stop.

940
00:56:12,680 --> 00:56:14,560
What's up with you?

941
00:56:14,640 --> 00:56:17,280
Did the doctor already let
you out of the hospital?

942
00:56:17,320 --> 00:56:20,000
Why are you out driving around in the
hot sun like this? You're gonna collapse.

943
00:56:21,800 --> 00:56:23,120
Well, well.

944
00:56:23,160 --> 00:56:24,320
Who would've known.

945
00:56:24,320 --> 00:56:28,240
that you actually care about me too.

946
00:56:28,760 --> 00:56:31,240
Who said I care about you?

947
00:56:31,320 --> 00:56:32,800
I care about P'Klao.

948
00:56:32,840 --> 00:56:35,000
I'm worried she'll lose one of her minions.

949
00:56:41,200 --> 00:56:42,280
Jae Nokkaew.

950
00:56:42,960 --> 00:56:44,280
I have to go now.

951
00:56:44,600 --> 00:56:46,000
Please take care of P'Klao.

952
00:56:46,040 --> 00:56:48,120
Pidpee and Muedmon too.

953
00:56:48,280 --> 00:56:50,120
Jon and Pao too.

954
00:56:51,600 --> 00:56:53,120
You have to love P'Klao a lot.

955
00:56:53,800 --> 00:56:54,920
Smile a lot too.

956
00:56:55,880 --> 00:56:57,840
No one's gonna annoy you anymore.

957
00:56:58,160 --> 00:57:00,480
Wait. Hold on, you little leech.
Where are you going?

958
00:57:00,480 --> 00:57:02,120
I'm not accepting any deliveries.

959
00:57:02,280 --> 00:57:03,920
You and I have different jobs.

960
00:57:03,960 --> 00:57:05,280
Who's gonna do all that for you?

961
00:57:05,920 --> 00:57:07,240
Come on now.

962
00:57:07,280 --> 00:57:10,200
We're friends.
Helping each other a little won't hurt.

963
00:57:10,200 --> 00:57:11,480
I'm heading out now.

964
00:57:11,480 --> 00:57:13,840
Hey. Wait up, you little leech.

965
00:57:16,400 --> 00:57:18,160
Woo-hoo.

966
00:57:19,120 --> 00:57:21,520
Where are you going?
We haven't finished talking yet.

967
00:57:21,520 --> 00:57:22,880
Hey, you little leech.

968
00:57:22,920 --> 00:57:25,040
Cow leech, buffalo leech,
chicken leech. Hey, stop.

969
00:57:25,040 --> 00:57:26,320
Jiw.

970
00:57:57,120 --> 00:57:58,120
P'Klao.

971
00:58:06,840 --> 00:58:08,400
Are you okay?

972
00:58:11,280 --> 00:58:12,360
Just now.

973
00:58:14,720 --> 00:58:16,880
I dreamed about Jiw.

974
00:58:18,200 --> 00:58:19,880
He said he was leaving.

975
00:58:20,680 --> 00:58:22,240
I don't know where he was going.

976
00:58:23,200 --> 00:58:24,200
And then.

977
00:58:24,280 --> 00:58:26,800
he asked me to take care of you.

978
00:58:35,640 --> 00:58:36,720
Hey.

979
00:58:49,680 --> 00:58:51,920
Jiw looked like he was hurting.

980
00:58:52,040 --> 00:58:53,040
Hey.

981
00:58:53,400 --> 00:58:55,120
Jiw...

982
00:59:04,120 --> 00:59:05,800
Did he die?

983
00:59:45,960 --> 00:59:48,400
You've signed everything already,
so you can go now.

984
00:59:48,440 --> 00:59:50,480
And how are you planning
to pay me those ten million?

985
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:51,800
Hurry up, hurry up.

986
00:59:53,680 --> 00:59:56,240
Why are you paying the dowry yourself anyway?

987
00:59:56,520 --> 00:59:57,680
Were you scared you
wouldn't get married?

988
00:59:57,720 --> 01:00:00,640
Wow, your car seats are so soft.

989
01:00:00,680 --> 01:00:02,080
P'Klao.

990
01:00:02,080 --> 01:00:05,240
My mom said you raise buffaloes too?

991
01:00:05,240 --> 01:00:08,200
I only went to Bangkok for
a few days to supervise construction.

992
01:00:08,240 --> 01:00:10,160
and women were already
showing up at your house?

993
01:00:10,200 --> 01:00:13,040
What's wrong with you?
Why are you being so ridiculous?

994
01:00:13,160 --> 01:00:15,240
Being jealous of my girlfriend
is ridiculous now?

995
01:00:20,040 --> 01:00:22,080
Slate it, please.

996
01:00:22,120 --> 01:00:23,480
-Tap Bear's face. Wait, wait, wait.
-Tap the face.

997
01:00:23,520 --> 01:00:25,120
I wanna look sad, but...

998
01:00:25,120 --> 01:00:26,440
I look too cool.
(I'm not addicted to being cool. Coolness is addicted to me.)

999
01:00:26,480 --> 01:00:27,480
Your tears are still flowing.

1000
01:00:28,440 --> 01:00:30,120
My tears are still flowing.

1001
01:00:30,160 --> 01:00:32,440
-But I'm stuck being cool.
-Addicted to coolness.

1002
01:00:33,280 --> 01:00:34,320
(One quick kiss delivered.)

1003
01:00:35,920 --> 01:00:37,240
-Cut.
-You moved so fast.

1004
01:00:37,240 --> 01:00:38,200
-So fast.
-I was rushing.

1005
01:00:38,200 --> 01:00:39,320
I kept hearing the walkie-talkie.

1006
01:00:39,360 --> 01:00:41,360
I was upstairs. Up on the truck.

1007
01:00:41,400 --> 01:00:43,200
-I was on the speaker.
-Do you have a clip for me to watch?

1008
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:49,040
(Sis is having the time of her life.)
